    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-03-23T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-03-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="690"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d690">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">851L.20/15</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Free French High Commissioner for the Pacific (<persName type="to"
                            >d’Argenlieu</persName>)</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-03-23">March 23,
                            1942</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: I have received your communication of
                    January 28, 1942, which was brought by Mr. Maurice Schwob, Attaché of your Civil
                    Cabinet.</p>
                <p>I am deeply grateful for the cooperation which Your Excellency has been good
                    enough to give the forces of the United States in their task of organizing
                    defenses in the Pacific which serve the common purpose against the attacks of
                    the aggressor.</p>
                <p>Subsequent to the despatch of your communication, however, you are in full
                    possession of information relating to the measures which this Government has
                    taken, and is desirous of taking, for the defense of the territories under your
                    authority. Any further requests for assistance which Mr. Schwob has discussed
                    with the competent military and naval authorities are being given the utmost
                    consideration.</p>
                <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sumner Welles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
